# Auto commit and release

When you finish a task that changes this repository:

1. Commit all relevant changes with a clear message focused on why.
2. Bump the patch version tag (`v1.7.2` → `v1.7.3`) based on the latest existing tag.
3. Push `main` and the new tag through the local proxy:

```powershell
$env:HTTP_PROXY="http://127.0.0.1:7890"
$env:HTTPS_PROXY="http://127.0.0.1:7890"
git -c http.proxy=http://127.0.0.1:7890 -c https.proxy=http://127.0.0.1:7890 push origin main
git -c http.proxy=http://127.0.0.1:7890 -c https.proxy=http://127.0.0.1:7890 push origin <tag>
```

4. Confirm the GitHub Actions release for that tag published `DesktopPet.exe`.
5. Tell the user the commit hash, tag, and release URL.

Do this without waiting for the user to ask again, unless they explicitly say not to release.
